He went out to cut something. So I took a look to see how it's going. It's far from being finished :(
More than 7 pages on chapter five. It remains my favorite chapter, and it's fairly done. A few layout changes, and minor changes to switch to the active voice and improve concision. To be said, I'd gladly take a break and a cup of tea, but the guy is still tinkering in my kitchen.
He's just started vacuuming again. I hope that's a good sign.
The craftsman has left.
He told me that he had drawn up a plan for the entire floor, but the owners were stingy and only paid for the small damaged area near the door. It's much better.
The house feels airy, and my air purifier is running in the kitchen while I enjoy a cup of tea in the garden.
